{
  "page": "Blood Betrayal",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>The <b>Blood Betrayal</b> was an event in <a href=\"/index.php/Yi_Ti\" title=\"Yi Ti\">YiTish</a> myth that ushered in the <a href=\"/index.php/Long_Night\" title=\"Long Night\">Long Night</a> and the subsequent fall of the <a href=\"/index.php/Great_Empire_of_the_Dawn\" title=\"Great Empire of the Dawn\">Great Empire of the Dawn</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiaf_yi_ti.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiaf_yi_ti.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Blood_Betrayal&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The <a href=\"/index.php/Opal_Emperor\" title=\"Opal Emperor\">Opal Emperor</a> was the seventh ruler of a line that began with the <a href=\"/index.php/God-on-Earth\" title=\"God-on-Earth\">God-on-Earth</a>, the son of the <a href=\"/index.php/Maiden-Made-of-Light\" title=\"Maiden-Made-of-Light\">Maiden-Made-of-Light</a> and the <a href=\"/index.php/Lion_of_Night\" title=\"Lion of Night\">Lion of Night</a>. He was succeeded by his daughter, the <a href=\"/index.php/Amethyst_Empress\" title=\"Amethyst Empress\">Amethyst Empress</a>, but her younger brother, envious, cast her down and <a href=\"/index.php/Kinslaying\" title=\"Kinslaying\">slew her</a>, taking the crown and proclaiming himself the <a href=\"/index.php/Bloodstone_Emperor\" title=\"Bloodstone Emperor\">Bloodstone Emperor</a>. He turned his back on the gods of Yi Ti and began worshiping a <a href=\"/index.php/Black_stone\" title=\"Black stone\">black stone</a> that had fallen from the skies, took a <a href=\"/index.php/Tiger-men\" title=\"Tiger-men\">tiger-woman</a> as wife, practiced <a href=\"/index.php/Cannibalism\" title=\"Cannibalism\">cannibalism</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Necromancy\" title=\"Necromancy\">necromancy</a>, and <a href=\"/index.php/Slavery\" title=\"Slavery\">enslaved</a> his own people. Horrified at the Blood Betrayal, the Maiden-Made-of-Light turned her back upon the world and the <a href=\"/index.php/Lion_of_Night\" title=\"Lion of Night\">Lion of Night</a> came forth in all his fury to punish the wickedness of man.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiaf_yi_ti.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiaf_yi_ti.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Blood_Betrayal&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rtwoiaf_yi_ti.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiaf_yi_ti.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">1.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiaf_yi_ti.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\">1.1</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i>, Yi Ti.</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20260404004608\nCache expiry: 1209600\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.011 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.013 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 176/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 8572/1000000\nPost‐expand incl